0.1 download driver
$wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/torvalds/linux/refs/heads/master/drivers/net/phy/microchip_t1s.c

1. build driver:
$make

2. load driver into kernel
$sudo chmod +x loadDriverIntoKernel.sh
$./loadDriverIntoKernel.sh

3. Insert two EVB-LAN8670-USB
4. determine Network names of devices
$ip a

5. This script sets up two 10BASE-T1 Ethernet interfaces on a Linux PC and configures the PLCA (Physical Layer Collision Avoidance) parameters for both.
Modify these according to result of "$ ip a" and set desired IP Addresses in configureEthernetDevices.sh:
# --- Interface 1 ---coordinator
IF1="enx6827199267cd"
IP1="192.168.10.11/24"
NODE_ID1=0

# --- Interface 2 ---follower
IF2="enx6827199270d1"
IP2="192.168.10.12/24"
NODE_ID2=1

$sudo chmod +x configureEthernetDevices.sh
$./configureEthernetDevices.sh

6. build application
$cd app
$make

7. in run_test.sh modify according to results of "$ip a":
RECEIVER_IF="enx6827199270d1"
SENDER_IF="enx6827199267cd"
DEST_MAC="68:27:19:92:70:d1"  # MAC-Adresse des Receivers

8. run test
$sudo chmod +x run_test.sh
$./run_test.h